"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-19-olympic-cyclist-found-dead-home-choking-food-21450487\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A five-timeOlympicathlete has been found dead inside her apartment after she reportedly choked on her food.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniela Larreal Chirinos was reported missing by colleagues on August 12 after failing to show up at the hotel where she worked in Las Vegas.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 109, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Larreal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daniela Larreal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Larreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Larreal\"}, {\"begin\": 125, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonny_Chirinos\", \"score\": 0.9999529262106671, \"rank\": 4.7075740512339937e-05, \"text\": \"Chirinos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonny_Chirinos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonny_Chirinos\"}, {\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\", \"score\": 0.9853392835037936, \"rank\": 0.01467847766645011, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Police officers discovered the 50-year-old's lifeless body four days later when they broke into her home to check on her.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An autopsy carried out by state authorities in Nevada found solid food remains lodged in Larreal's windpipe and is thought to have died of asphyxiation.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 422, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"score\": 0.9996622792734153, \"rank\": 0.0003378348047738956, \"text\": \"Nevada\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Investigations are still ongoing and her official cause of death has not yet been confirmed but Larreal is believed to have been dead since August 11.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track cyclist is one of Venezuela's most illustrious sports stars and is the nation's only athlete to have competed in five different Olympic Games between 1992 and 2012.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite never clinching a podium finish at the Olympics, Larreal was awarded four diplomas - a certificate handed to the top eight finishers in a competition at the Games.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Larreal also won numerous gold medals during her career, including at the Pan American Games and South American Games.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9890407725372701, \"rank\": 0.00650000168100202, \"text\": \"Pan American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_American_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999996775841, \"rank\": 3.2200103116673144e-10, \"text\": \"South American Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_American_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After London 2012, Larreal publicly opposed Venezuela's president Nicolas Maduro when he took over from Hugo Chaves and accused the new government's Ministry of Sports of corruption.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"After London\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\"}, {\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}, {\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"score\": 0.9999999836136341, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Maduro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\"}, {\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\", \"score\": 0.9999973879323543, \"rank\": 2.6120742810896438e-06, \"text\": \"Chaves\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.D._Chaves\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went on to become an activist who persistently stood up for 'freedom and democracy', effectively claiming Venezuela had become a dictatorship.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Larreal's criticism of Maduro and the government led to her being subjected to death threats, so she fled her home country in exile and moved to the USA.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997291934417, \"rank\": 2.1413950594378938e-07, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not stop her from campaigning and even her last Instagram post on August 8 referenced the ongoing political unrest in Venezuela following Maduro's disputed victory in July's election.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9665136988180258, \"rank\": 0.03464648351084879, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuelan_presidential_crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politician Henrique Capriles paid tribute to 'a great figure in cycling' and 'specialist in track events'.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Henrique Capriles\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrique_Capriles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He wrote on X: 'Daniela, in addition to winning medals, stood out for being the only Venezuelan to have participated in five Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1957, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"score\": 0.9999999151973533, \"rank\": 5.3076257187403833e-08, \"text\": \"Daniela\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A glory of sport!\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I join in the mourning that afflicts the country and send my heartfelt words of condolence to her family, friends and those who were her teammates in her sporting career.\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"May god receive Daniela in eternal rest.'\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"score\": 0.9999999151973533, \"rank\": 5.3076257187403833e-08, \"text\": \"Daniela\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:'I hope you understand' - Olympics star defects to Team GB after Paris 2024  ArrowMORE:Team GB Paris Olympics hero angers rival with 'classless' celebration  ArrowMORE:Eddie Hearn offers to promote Imane Khelif after Olympic boxing gender row  Punchy ana